result.execSummary:
The defendant FREDRICK ROBERTSON was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case. On one or more other charges, FREDRICK ROBERTSON was found not guilty. These charges were not proven and have no legal effect. FREDRICK ROBERTSON is presumed innocent of the not guilty charges.

  • FREDRICK ROBERTSON was found guilty of Possession of Narcotic Drugs, a class I felony, Wisconsin Statutes 961.41(3g)(am).
  • FREDRICK ROBERTSON was found guilty of Pandering-Facilitation, a class A misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 944.33(2).
  • FREDRICK ROBERTSON was found guilty of Receive Compensation for Human Trafficking, a class F felony, Wisconsin Statutes 940.302(2)(c).

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

superMiscConds.notes: The Court ordered that all court costs, fines, restitution & surcharges be paid through collection by the Department of Corrections from 25% of funds under Sec. 973.05(4)(b) and as a condition of extended supervision.

Complete compas assessment,  counseling, evaluations, programs and assessments as appropriate and followup.  Pay supervisory fees as determined by the Department of Corrections.  Defendant shall provide a DNA sample by calling the Work Release Unit  at 920-232-1915 or 920-232-1919 WITHIN 72 HOURS OF SENTENCING to set up an appointment.   The Work Release Units hours are 8:00 am-4:00 pm/Monday thru Friday. Defendant shall provide proof of identification along with the court minutes stating a DNA sample is required.  Failure to comply with this order may result in either a finding of contempt of court or a criminal charge of Failure to Provide a DNA Sample pursuant to Wis. Stats. 946.52.
